{"type":"message","id":"fcf67ade","parentId":"bb545ebd","timestamp":"2026-06-03T02:56:39.761Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"汀桑 is asking why the morningcourt timed out - speculating if it's because 8:00 is peak request time for the DeepSeek API. This is a valid guess but let me think about it more practically.\n\nThe error was \"cron: job execution timed out (last phase: model-call-started)\" at 302,681ms with a 300s timeout. So the model call started but didn't finish within ~5 minutes.\n\nFor DeepSeek V4 Flash, it could be:\n1. API congestion at peak hours (08:00 Beijing time could be a busy period)\n2. The model itself being slow for the complex task (reading files, generating a story, etc.)\n3. A transient issue\n\n08:00 Beijing time is UTC+8, so that's 00:00 UTC - which could be a time when DeepSeek's API sees a lot of traffic from other time zones as well.\n\nLet me just reply casually.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"啧 有可能。八点正好是国内上班高峰，DeepSeek 那边请求量最大。\n\n也不算故意卡你，就是人多排队久——刚好排到你这超了那两秒。\n\n现在改到 600s 应该够了，除非它直接挂掉不回，那就不关 timeout 的事了。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":6207,"output":265,"cacheRead":24448,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":200,"totalTokens":30920,"cost":{"input":0.0008689800000000001,"output":0.0000742,"cacheRead":0.0006845439999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001627724}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780455395331,"responseId":"9c64d393-e3a5-4afd-9438-47b26a6f7028"}}
