{"type":"message","id":"5bc74f39","parentId":"3ff60c3e","timestamp":"2026-06-03T11:49:30.042Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK I see what's happening. Looking at the conversation history, the sequence is clear:\n\n1. User sends `/画图 符合此要求`\n2. I ask what requirement, then spawn Son for Liang Wenfeng poster\n3. I yield\n4. User says \"不是\"\n5. I reply \"哈？不是梁文锋？那你说清楚啊😓\"\n6. Then the system shows a conversation info block with my bingo reply quoted.\n\nThe conversation info block at the top (\"—OL、空姐、文学少女……挺会挑啊你。剩下的格子留着下次再战？\") is just system context — it's showing what I previously said to help contextualize the current turn.\n\nSo the user's ACTUAL latest message is \"不是\" which I already replied to. There's no new user message. But wait, the conversation info block is shown at the top of my context. This is the standard system behavior of showing the previous message context.\n\nSo I should just continue. The user said \"不是\" and I already asked them to clarify. But since this is a new turn and my reply to \"不是\" was already sent... I think I need to wait for the user's next message.\n\nActually, looking at the runtime state more carefully:\n- The conversation info block is shown as part of the Dynamic Project Context\n- It was shown as a \"Quoted message\" at the top, quoting my own bingo reply\n\nThis is probably because the QQ bot is showing the last message context. The user sent a new message of \"不是\" and it arrived while I was yielded. I replied to it. Now the system is showing me the next turn.\n\nWait, but the last tool call in the sessions history is still my `sessions_history` call. So I haven't finished processing this turn yet. Let me figure out what to respond now.\n\nThe user said \"不是\" and I replied \"哈？不是梁文锋？那你说清楚啊😓\". But now I need to wait for their answer. Since there's no new message from the user, I shouldn't generate another response. But it seems like I'm in a new turn with the conversation info block shown as context.\n\nHmm, actually I think the system is showing me the conversation info as context because I'm in a new turn after sending my reply to \"不是\". But there's no new user message. I should just wait for the user to respond.\n\nLet me just tell the user I'm waiting for their clarification.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"行吧，我搞混了。\n\n你说「符合此要求」——指的是哪个要求？说清楚我再让 Son 画😓"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":3796,"output":545,"cacheRead":42624,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":516,"totalTokens":46965,"cost":{"input":0.00053144,"output":0.00015260000000000002,"cacheRead":0.001193472,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001877512}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780487363908,"responseId":"d731fdd3-7268-46de-afa1-d8bfb418c37e"}}
