{"type":"message","id":"dd8c380f","parentId":"31597f0a","timestamp":"2026-06-03T11:54:23.702Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see:\n\n1. **Task 1 (空姐)**: `b51b158e` - runId `video_generate:7adbd458-6796-4f94-acb8-e5c744ccb350:error` - This means Son tried to use video_generate tool and got an error. Model: `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash` - but I specified `dashscope/qwen3-vl-flash`! It seems my override wasn't applied.\n\nWait, looking at the session_spawn calls I made:\n- First spawn (OL goddess): I specified model=`dashscope/qwen3-vl-flash` - this is task 4 `6c98321f`\n- Second spawn (空姐): I specified model=`dashscope/qwen3-vl-flash` - this is task 2 `a47036ad` but it shows model `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash`! Hmm, maybe the model override wasn't working properly.\n\nWait, task 2 shows model `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash` and runId `video_generate:78e0083e-e9e7-4ed2-b87e-95fd693cc1cc:error`. That's weird.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at tasks 1 and 2 (b51b158e and a47036ad), they both show model `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash` and have `video_generate:...:error` in the runId. That means:\n- Son is using DeepSeek v4 flash (not qwen3-vl-flash) for these tasks\n- DeepSeek v4 flash doesn't have image generation capability, so it's falling back to video_generate tool\n- video_generate tool is for video, not images, so it's erroring\n\nTasks 3 and 4 (86f7a943 and d3807ce6) show model `dashscope/qwen3-vl-flash` and have plain runId without error prefix. These seem to be working (qwen3-vl-flash can do image generation).\n\nSo the issue is: I specified `dashscope/qwen3-vl-flash` for all spawns, but for some reason tasks 1 and 2 ended up using `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash`. This might be because:\n- The model name I specified has a typo? Let me check: I wrote `dashscope/qwen3-vl-flash` which is correct.\n- Or maybe the first two didn't get the override?\n\nWait, let me re-check. I spawned 4 tasks in total:\n1. First spawn for OL -