{"type":"message","id":"cb5756dc","parentId":"52b34320","timestamp":"2026-06-03T11:54:39.966Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the image generation using qwen3-vl-flash (dashscope) is failing with a 401 Invalid API-key error. This means the API key for Alibaba Cloud DashScope (通义千问) is either missing, expired, or invalid.\n\nThe user is asking what this means. Let me explain.\n\nThe situation is:\n1. I tried to use `dashscope/qwen3-vl-flash` for image generation\n2. The model responded saying video generation failed with HTTP 401 Invalid API-key\n3. This means the DashScope API key configured in the system is not valid\n\nSince the first task (Liang Wenfeng poster, task 5) used `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash` and completed successfully (it's marked as \"done\"), that means DeepSeek works fine. But qwen3-vl-flash's API key is invalid.\n\nThe earlier \"video\" error was because qwen3-vl-flash tried to use the image generation but the API key was bad. The system tried video_generate as a fallback but also failed.\n\nSo the root cause: **Alibaba DashScope (通义千问) 的 API Key 无效或过期了。**\n\nLet me check if there's a way to verify this or fix it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Dashboard 的 API Key 废了。\n\n意思就是 **通义千问的密钥过期或失效了**——画图的模型 qwen3-vl 走的就是阿里那条线，Key 不对所以画不出来。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_uNKNFDGTJM7SiYorddDg2027","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"dashscope\\|DASHSCOPE\\|qwen\\|QWEN\" ~/.openclaw/gateway/config* 2>/dev/null | head -20; grep -r \"dashscope\\|DASHSCOPE\\|qwen\\|QWEN\" ~/.openclaw/gateway/.env* 2>/dev/null | head -5; echo \"---\"; cat ~/.openclaw/gateway/config.yml 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"dashscope\\|qwen\\|ali\\|alibaba\" | head -10"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"grep -r \\\"dashscope\\\\|DASHSCOPE\\\\|qwen\\\\|QWEN\\\" ~/.openclaw/gateway/config* 2>/dev/null | head -20; grep -r \\\"dashscope\\\\|DASHSCOPE\\\\|qwen\\\\|QWEN\\\" ~/.openclaw/gateway/.env* 2>/dev