{"type":"message","id":"46e3b890","parentId":"c2ee4841","timestamp":"2026-06-03T11:55:31.814Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The OL task (d3807ce6) also completed with \"32 tool call(s) made without visible output\" - which means it ran but didn't produce a visible result. It was using `dashscope/qwen3-vl-flash` which has the API key issue.\n\nMeanwhile, the 空姐 task (a47036ad) completed successfully with an output image.\n\nSo the situation is:\n- OL task (the one the user actually wants) - failed due to DashScope API key issue\n- 空姐 task - succeeded (it was on deepseek model which used some other image gen?)\n- Other tasks still running or failing\n\nLet me look at the details. The OL image task used qwen3-vl-flash and failed. The 空姐 task used deepseek-v4-flash but somehow produced an image - probably because deepseek fell back to some other tool.\n\nI need to retry the OL image generation. Since qwen3-vl-flash's API key is broken, I should try using a different model or approach. Maybe I can use the `wanx2.1-t2i-turbo` model which seemed to work for the 空姐 task, or try a different image generation provider.\n\nWait, actually the 空姐 task that showed model as deepseek-v4-flash but still produced an image... Let me check what happened. The result from the earlier completion event said the 空姐 image was generated with `wanx2.1-t2i-turbo`. So Son's draw implementation might try multiple models/providers and fall back if one fails.\n\nFor the OL image, it ran on qwen3-vl-flash and produced \"32 tool call(s) made without visible output\" - meaning it kept calling tools but never got a valid image output.\n\nLet me try spawning the OL task again but bypass the model specification so Son can figure out which image gen works.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"OL 那张跑了 5 分钟但没出图——qwen3-vl 的 API Key 有问题导致画不出来。\n\n但空姐那张倒是跑成了。我换个路子再跑一次 OL——"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_e7Moc9DCdETGoVwjOxbS0722","name":"