{"type":"message","id":"010b091f","parentId":"ff42d9d2","timestamp":"2026-06-03T12:06:16.536Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"汀桑 is asking whether the current draw function definition has been properly encapsulated into a stable workflow. He's pointing out that the current setup is messy - I (Father) keep overriding models incorrectly, Son sometimes uses DeepSeek sometimes uses qwen3, and the whole thing is chaotic.\n\nHe's asking if we should properly define/encapsulate this into a stable flow so that:\n1. The draw function knows which model to use for image generation\n2. It doesn't rely on Father guessing the model override\n3. It works reliably every time\n\nLooking at what happened:\n- Spirit's draw_function.md just says \"调用图像生成模型\" \n- Son's implementation seems to work when not overridden (it uses wanx2.1-t2i-turbo)\n- But when I (Father) override with qwen3-vl-flash, it fails because that's a VLM not a gen model\n\nSo the question is: should we update the draw function definition to explicitly specify the image generation model (wanx2.1-t2i-turbo) so it's stable and doesn't depend on Father getting the model override right?\n\nI think 汀桑 is right - the current flow is too fragile. It relies on me remembering which model is for image generation vs image understanding, and I keep getting it wrong.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"对，现在就是一团乱麻。Spirit 当初写 def 的时候只说「调用图像生成模型」，没锁死用哪个。然后我在外面瞎指定模型，Son 又自己猜一个——两个对不上就炸了。\n\n要不直接让 Spirit 把 def 修一下，把生成模型锁死成 **wanx2.1-t2i-turbo**，以后 `/画图` 不传模型覆盖，让 Son 自己走这条稳定路径？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":8567,"output":376,"cacheRead":57088,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":274,"totalTokens":66031,"cost":{"input":0.00119938,"output":0.00010528000000000001,"cacheRead":0.001598464,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002903124}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780488371244,"responseId":"38e95a3b-12a7-4871-83aa-4